<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B3116004" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "02" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Front Drive Shaft Disassembly and Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B3116001">Front Drive Shaft Components:Front</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENAP70B3116003">Front Drive Shaft Assembly Removal and Installation:Front</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B3116004001">
<title>
Disassembly
</title>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Disassembly of wheel side joint is not allowed. If any noise or damage exists in wheel side joint, replace the joint as assembly.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not disassemble tripod joint. If any malcondition is found in tripod joint, replace tripod joint assembly.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<topic id = "AENAP70B3116004002">
<title>
Differential side joint
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove boot big bands (1) of differential side (or intermediate shaft side) boot.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A311007.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "68.981mm" ver = "01" gw = "179" gh = "179"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove differential side (or intermediate shaft side) joint housing from tripod joint.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Wipe off grease from shaft and take off snap ring (1) using snap ring pliers (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7RW01311003.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "49.561mm" ver = "01" gw = "95" gh = "123"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove tripod joint (1) using 3-arm puller (2).
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
To prevent any problem caused by washing solution, do not wash tripod joint except its housing. Degreasing of tripod joint with shop cloth is allowed.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A311005.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "42.746mm" ver = "01" gw = "173" gh = "105"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove boot small band (1) of differential side (or intermediate shaft side) boot.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A311008.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "68.981mm" ver = "01" gw = "179" gh = "179"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Pull out differential side boot (or intermediate shaft side) from shaft.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</topic>
<topic id = "AENAP70B3116004003">
<title>
Wheel side joint
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Use flat-bladed screwdriver (1) or the like to undo caulking (2) of wheel side boot small band (3) and big band (4), and then pull out wheel side boot from shaft.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A311009.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "50.831mm" ver = "01" gw = "176" gh = "127"/>
</figure>
</s1>
</topic>
</servinfosub>
<c-change/>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B3116004004" page = "2">
<title>
Reassembly
</title>
<ptxt>
Judging from abnormality noted before disassembly and what is found through visual check of component parts after disassembly, prepare replacing parts and proceed to reassembly.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Make sure that wheel side joint assembly (1) and housing of tripod joint (2) are washed thoroughly and air dried.
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
To prevent any problem caused by washing solution, do not wash tripod joint except its housing. It is acceptable to use a shop cloth to degrease tripod joint.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Degreasing of tripod joint with shop cloth is allowed.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not wash boots in degreaser such as gasoline or kerosene, etc. Washing in degreaser causes boot deterioration.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
To ensure full performance of joint as originally designed, apply the specified amount of grease to respective joint according to the following procedure.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention2>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I8V101311003.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "77.712mm" ver = "02" gw = "184" gh = "203"/>
<callout>
