<topic id = "AENAP70B3116004005">
<title>
Wheel side joint
</title>
<s1 page = "2">
<ptxt>
Wash disassembled parts (except boots). After washing parts, air dry them completely. 
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean boots with shop cloth.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Apply grease from the service kit to wheel side joint.
</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>
Grease specification for wheel side joint of front drive shaft
</title>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "3" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.980in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "0.745in"/>
<colspec colnum = "3" colname = "3" colwidth = "1.736in"/>
<thead>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Transaxle type
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Grease color
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Grease amount
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "1">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
M/T
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Tan
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
45 – 65 g (1.59 – 2.29 oz)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
A/T
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
Tan
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "3" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "1">
<ptxt>
35 – 55 g (1.24 – 1.94 oz)
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install wheel side boot on shaft.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Fill boot inside with specified grease.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Insert flat-bladed screwdriver into boot (2) and allow air to enter boot so that air pressure in boot becomes the same as the atmospheric pressure.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I8G001311012.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "40.492mm" ver = "01" gw = "151" gh = "98"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Place new boot big band (3) and small band (4) onto wheel side boot so that outer end (1) of each band faces in forward rotating direction (2) as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Be sure to use new boot bands.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not squeeze or distort boot when fastening boot with boot bands. Squeezing boot to force air out may distort boot and reduce its durability.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I4RS0A310009.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "91.005mm" ver = "01" gw = "135" gh = "241"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Fasten boot big band (2) and boot small band (1) using special tool as shown in figure
</ptxt>
<attention2>
<ptxt>
Do not squeeze or distort boot when fastening boot with boot bands. Squeezing boot to force air out may distort boot and reduce its durability.
</ptxt>
</attention2>
<spec>
<title>
Boot band fastening distance “a”
</title>
<ptxt>
:1.2 – 4.0 mm (0.048 – 0.157 in.)
</ptxt>
</spec>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A101">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09943-57011">
09943–57011
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70A311011.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "52.951mm" ver = "02" gw = "186" gh = "134"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
</topic>
<topic id = "AENAP70B3116004006">
<title>
Differential side joint
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Wash disassembled parts (except boots). After washing parts, air dry them completely.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Clean boots with shop cloth.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install differential side (or intermediate shaft side) boot on shaft.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install tripod joint (1) on shaft using special tool with hammer, directing its chamfered spline (3) toward wheel side, and then fasten tripod joint with new snap ring (2) using snap ring pliers (4).
</ptxt>
<servicetool>
<servicetoolitem id = "L3A102">
<s-part>
(A)
</s-part>
<s-number num = "09925-98221">
09925–98221
</s-number>
<ptxt>
</ptxt>
</servicetoolitem>
</servicetool>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I8G001311014.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "30.306mm" ver = "01" gw = "155" gh = "69"/>
</figure>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I8C50A311007.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "50.196mm" ver = "01" gw = "189" gh = "125"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<c-change/>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Using specified grease included in spare parts, apply grease “A” to tripod joint, differential side joint housing (1) and boot.
</ptxt>
<spec>
